                &lt;h3>&#xD;
                    Introduction&#xD;
                &lt;/h3>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    The architecture models are defined using three basic views (i.e. Business, Logical, and Technology)&#xD;
                    and with more or less detail as required. It is important to ensure that relationships, definitions,&#xD;
                    and other aspects of these models are maintained and remain consistent throughout the models. A tool&#xD;
                    can also ensure consistency between IT architectures defined in various contexts within the enterprise,&#xD;
                    and provide the clear linkages between components in these different models.&amp;#160;&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
