&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Discussion&amp;#160;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Enterprise architectures tend to (and should) become more complex over time, as more detail is added through reviews&#xD;
    and updates. A tool can greatly assist in managing this complexity while at the same time providing views of the models&#xD;
    at any required level of detail and tailored to the audience at hand. Discovery of unknown patterns or relationships is&#xD;
    also facilitated, providing more insight into the architecture. Most modeling tools support the application of modeling&#xD;
    patterns or profiles that greatly aid and speed up the modeling process while ensuring the proper application of these&#xD;
    profiles and patterns. The end result is better, more consistent and more comprehensible to the target audience.&amp;#160;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This relates very much to &quot;continuous quality improvement&quot;,&amp;#160;where quality can be greatly improved through the use&#xD;
    of not only a good process but also through the use of a modeling tool that will help in following the process and help&#xD;
    in creating, maintaining and communicating the architectural models.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
